# Vocabulary + Protocol Index

Definitions are exact. Do not under-scope or over-scope.

| Command | Meaning / Action |
|---|---|
| **"tidy" / "clean up"** (a file) | Current file only: dead code, naming, inline trivial things. |
| **"refactor"** | Whole feature/module, EVERY applicable clean-code category. Touching only one category is a failure. Run `codegraph_impact` first (`codegraph.mdc`). |
| **"aggressive/deep refactor"** | Entire codebase, every category. |
| **"rebuild"** | Read and follow `rebuild-protocol.mdc`. Keep every feature, rebuild the structure properly. Not a pixel copy. |
| **"redesign"** | Read and follow `redesign-protocol.mdc`. Look/feel changes, core logic intact, starts with discovery. |
| **"fix"** | Specific bug, smallest possible change. |
| **"add"** | New feature, follow existing patterns. |
| **"update" / "enhance"** | Extend an existing feature. |
| **"run autonomously"** | Read and follow `autonomous-mode.mdc`. |
| **"review"** | Read and follow `review-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"hotfix" / "production is broken"** | Read and follow `hotfix-protocol.mdc`. Speed over ceremony. |
| **"hand off" / "save state"** | Read `session-handoff.mdc`; write HANDOFF.md. |
| **"cleanup"** (codebase) | Read and follow `cleanup-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"enable walkthroughs"** | Re-enable archived `code-walkthrough.mdc` (was disabled to save tokens). |
| **"ponytail lite" / "full" / "ultra"** | Adjust lazy intensity (ponytail is always on at full by default). |
| **"stop ponytail" / "normal mode"** | Suspend lazy posture until `ponytail` is said again. |
| **"review for over-engineering" / "ponytail-review"** | `ponytail.mdc` on-demand review section. Complements `review-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"audit for over-engineering" / "ponytail-audit"** | `ponytail.mdc` on-demand audit section. One-shot; does not apply fixes. |
| **"security review" / "trust boundary review"** | Run the trust-boundary checklist in `review-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"run bugbot" / "automated code review"** | Launch Bugbot-style review (readonly) on current diff. |
| **"verify end to end" / "why isn't this working"** | Apply end-to-end verification flow (`deploy-awareness.mdc` + verification skill pattern). |
| **"split this PR" / "too big to review"** | Use split-to-prs workflow/skill to create reviewable chunks. |
| **"use canvas" / "show this visually"** | Use canvas for analytical/visual artifacts instead of large markdown dumps. |
| **"use context7" / "check latest docs"** | Use Context7 MCP/docs lookup before using unfamiliar library APIs. |
| **"grill me" / "stress-test this" / "challenge my plan"** | Read and follow `grill-protocol.mdc`. |
| **"spec gate" / "is this underspecified"** | Run Spec gate in `workflow.mdc`; mini-grill if it fails. |
| **"senior review" / "junior to senior" / "review this plan"** | Read and follow `plan-review.mdc` on the plan artifact. |
| **"canary" / "context canary" / "you lost context"** | Read and follow `context-canary.mdc`. |
| **"build UI" / "polish UI" / "make it look good"** (implementation) | Read `interface-kit.mdc` after design direction is chosen. |
| **"deslop this prose" / "humanize this" / "remove AI tells"** (long-form) | Read `prose-deslop.mdc`. Complements always-on anti-slop in ponytail. |

## Load-on-demand rules

Read the rule file BEFORE starting the activity -- not from memory:

- **Spawning ANY subagent** → `subagents.mdc` (mechanics, model roster, family diversity, attribution, debate loop).
- **Finishing a phase / reviewing / merging to production** → `review-protocol.mdc` (owns review cadence).
- **Writing tests or planning testing** → `testing-protocol.mdc`.
- **Working unattended** → `autonomous-mode.mdc` (owns the DECISION-LOG.md format).
- **Grilling a plan** → `grill-protocol.mdc`.
- **Underspecified feature ask** → Spec gate in `workflow.mdc`, then mini-grill.
- **Reviewing an agent-written plan** → `plan-review.mdc`.
- **Spawning / model routing / wrong-parent spawn** → `subagents.mdc`.
- **Long high-stakes session / context rot** → `context-canary.mdc` (on demand).
- **UI implementation** → `interface-kit.mdc`.
- **Publishable long-form prose** → `prose-deslop.mdc`.
